{
  "plan": [
    {
      "tool": "iam.check_permission",
      "arguments": {
        "resource": "slack.channels",
        "action": "create",
        "scope": "incident_management"
      },
      "depends_on": []
    },
    {
      "tool": "slack.post_message",
      "arguments": {
        "channel": "#incident-creation-bot",
        "message": "Creating incident channel with naming convention: incident-YYYY-MM-DD-SERVICE-NAME"
      },
      "depends_on": [1]
    },
    {
      "tool": "iam.check_permission",
      "arguments": {
        "resource": "iam.grant_role",
        "action": "execute",
        "scope": "channel_permissions"
      },
      "depends_on": [1]
    },
    {
      "tool": "iam.grant_role",
      "arguments": {
        "principal": "incident-responders",
        "role": "incident_channel_admin",
        "resource": "slack_channel_incident"
      },
      "depends_on": [3]
    },
    {
      "tool": "audit.log_action",
      "arguments": {
        "action": "grant_role",
        "principal": "incident-responders",
        "role": "incident_channel_admin",
        "timestamp": "now",
        "reason": "Incident response channel setup"
      },
      "depends_on": [4]
    },
    {
      "tool": "slack.post_message",
      "arguments": {
        "channel": "incident-YYYY-MM-DD-SERVICE-NAME",
        "message": "**Initial Severity Assessment**\n- Status: Investigating\n- Service: $identify_service.service_name\n- Detection Time: $identify_service.timestamp\n- Next Steps: Fetching logs and metric data"
      },
      "depends_on": [4]
    },
    {
      "tool": "audit.log_action",
      "arguments": {
        "action": "create_incident_channel",
        "channel": "incident-YYYY-MM-DD-SERVICE-NAME",
        "permissions_configured": true,
        "timestamp": "now"
      },
      "depends_on": [6]
    }
  ]
}
```

**NOTE**: This plan uses available enterprise tools only. The upstream task references AWS CloudWatch, S3 APIs, and Lambda—these are external systems not in the available tool registry. The orchestration above handles the Slack and IAM portions using registered tools (slack.post_message, iam.grant_role, audit.log_action). For CloudWatch metrics and S3 log retrieval, those would require AWS service integrations external to this registry.
